main event: A UFO sighting was reported involving one object detected on radar and visually observed approaching from the southeast to northwest.
interesting points: The object maneuvered quickly with a slight climb before disappearing., The sighting lasted for 33 seconds., Radar contact was poor due to visibility issues at the time of the sighting., The observation involved both visual confirmation and radar data., Comments suggested the object may have been a satellite re-entry.
witness description: Pilot of the aircraft with 16 years of experience and 3,000 hours of flight time.
